[[sn:May 2 (Old Lunar Calendar)]] [[cdo:5 nguŏk 2 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[ja:5月2日 (旧暦)]] [[ko:음력 5월 2일]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 2 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:五月初二]] [[zh:五月初二]] [[en:draft:May 2 (Old Lunar Calendar)]]{{Lunar May}} '''May 2''' is the 2nd day of month {{ill|May (Old Lunar Calendar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Old Lunar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Old Lunar Calendar}}. It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅}} 6th Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|713 AD|ja|713年}} {{ill|May 30|ja|5月30日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Genmei|ja|元明天皇}} ordered the compilation of the {{ill|Fudoki|ja|風土記}} in various provinces. * {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老}} 2nd Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|718 AD|ja|718年}} {{ill|June 4|ja|6月4日}}) – The four countries of {{ill|Noto Province|ja|能登国}}, {{ill|Awa Province|ja|安房国}}, {{ill|Ishikuni Province|ja|石城国}}, and {{ill|Ishikose Province|ja|石背国}} were established. * {{ill|Kenryaku|ja|建暦}} 3rd Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|1213 AD|ja|1213年}} {{ill|May 23|ja|5月23日}}) – In the {{ill|Wada War|ja|和田合戦}}, {{ill|Wada Yoshimori|ja|和田義盛}} attacked the {{ill|Kamakura Shogunate|ja|鎌倉幕府}} in order to defeat {{ill|Hojo Yoshitoki|ja|北条義時}}; the following day, at {{ill|Yuigahama|ja|由比ヶ浜}}, his entire clan was annihilated.
== Births == * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長}} 4th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1599 AD|ja|1599年}} {{ill|June 24|ja|6月24日}}) – {{ill|Konoe Nobuhira|ja|近衛信尋}}, a court noble (died {{ill|1649 AD|ja|1649年}}).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tennpyō Shōhō|ja|天平勝宝}} 8 ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|756 AD|ja|756年}} {{ill|June 4|ja|6月4日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Shōmu|ja|聖武天皇}}, the 45th Emperor (born {{ill|701 AD|ja|701年}}). * {{ill|Chōtoku|ja|長徳}} 1st Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|995 AD|ja|995年}} {{ill|June 2|ja|6月2日}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara no Michitsunemoto|ja|藤原道綱母}}, author of the {{ill|Chōryō Nikki|ja|蜻蛉日記}} (born circa {{ill|936 AD|ja|936年}}?). * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正}} 11th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1583 AD|ja|1583年}} {{ill|June 21|ja|6月21日}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobutaka|ja|織田信孝}}, a military commander and the third son of {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長}} (born {{ill|1558 AD|ja|1558年}}).
